parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electronic Control Unit (ECU) Communication Failure with Key Fob
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECU communication with the key fob can cause the engine to shut down while driving, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents, especially on high-speed roads.
symptoms: The engine shuts down unexpectedly while driving
the anti-theft system (Immobilizer) prevents the car from starting
the key fob ID is erased or not recognized
dashboard lights turn off
and an indicator light shows the immobilizer mode is on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to notify vehicle owners of open recalls in a timely and effective manner can lead to delayed repairs, putting the safety of drivers and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Owners are not notified of open recalls
notifications are not forwarded to new addresses
and owners are reliant on mail delivery for recall information.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high pressure fuel pump can cause the fuel control valve plunger to become stuck in the open position, leading to stalling, loss of control, and potential accidents, especially at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: Stalling
loss of control
engine hesitation
decreased engine performance
difficulty starting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Oil Consumption in GDI Engines
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, engine failure, and potentially cause accidents due to engine stalling or loss of power.
symptoms: Oil pressure light illuminates
engine stalling
oil level drops rapidly
frequent oil top-offs required
engine noise or knocking sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Warranty Dispute and Lack of Transparency
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dispute over warranty coverage can lead to frustration, financial burden, and delayed or neglected repairs, which can compromise vehicle safety and performance.
symptoms: Dealership and manufacturer disagree on warranty coverage
warranty claims denied despite meeting conditions
lack of transparency on warranty terms and conditions
conflicting information from dealership and manufacturer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake lights can increase the risk of a rear-end collision, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intention to stop.
symptoms: The rear brake lights do not illuminate
the brake lights do not function properly
the brake lights are dim or faint.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden extension of the brake pedal to the floorboard can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The brake pedal extends to the floorboard
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is difficult to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to start the engine in hot temperatures can leave the driver stranded, causing inconvenience and potentially leading to safety risks, especially in extreme weather conditions.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start immediately
requires multiple attempts to start
and may seem to return to normal functionality after starting. No warning lights are illuminated.
